    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="645"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d645">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">023.1/9–743</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-07">September 7,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for Hon. Cordell Hull</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Please speak to me about our publishing the notes of the conversations between
                    Wilson, Lloyd George and Clemenceau in Paris in 1919.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d645fn1">The reference is to the proposed publication of the minutes
                        of the meetings of the Council of Four in <ref target="frus1919Parisv01">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, The Paris Peace Conference,
                            1919</ref>. The British Government had been asked to clear the minutes
                        for publication, and Roosevelt’s interest in the subject presumably arose
                        from a conversation initiated by Churchill. Concerning further discussion of
                        the subject between Roosevelt and Churchill at Hyde Park on September 12,
                        1943, see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1338">p.
                        1338</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I have a distinct hesitation (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) because Lloyd George is
                    still alive and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) because notes of these conversations
                    ought not to have been taken down anyway.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
